    "name": "E-Credentialing CVO Platform — Public REST API v1 (v1.2.0)",
    "description": "The v1 surface is intentionally read-only. Every request requires\na Bearer API key with the appropriate scope; every request is\naudited; PHI fields (SSN, DOB, DEA, personal address, notes) are\nNEVER returned regardless of scope.\n\nFor a no-auth playground using synthetic data, see\n`/api/sandbox/v1/*` (documented at `/sandbox`).\n\nRate limiting (since v1.2.0): every successful response carries\n`X-RateLimit-Limit`, `X-RateLimit-Remaining`, and\n`X-RateLimit-Reset` headers (Unix-seconds). When you exceed the\nper-key budget the API returns a `429` with the `RateLimitProblem`\nbody and a `Retry-After` header. See `docs/api/versioning.md`\nfor the full contract and deprecation policy.\n\nWave 8 (2026-04-18). See ADR 0020 and `docs/qa/per-pillar/pillar-j-api.md`.\n\nAuto-generated from `docs/api/openapi-v1.yaml`.\nDo not hand-edit — regenerate via `npm run postman:gen`.",
